 its waters. Lifeguards came down with mysterious illnesses. And Howard Bennett happily swam in it every morning. By accident, Bennett learned that Los Angeles had applied for a waiver from the Clean Water Act to continue discharging sewage into the bay. Incensed that he had been swimming in dirty water, Bennett organized oddball coalition to orchestrate stunts such as wrapping brown ribbon around LA's city hall and issuing Dirty Toilet Awards to chastise the city's administration. This is the fast-paced story of how this unusual cast of characters created an environmental movement in Los Angeles that continues to this day with the nationally recognized Heal the Bay. Character-driven, compelling, and uplifting, Dirty Water tells how even the most polluted water can be cleaned up-by ordinary people.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEnvironmental policyzCaliforniazSanta Monica Bay Region. 0aEnvironmentalistszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aHigh school teacherszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aMarine pollutionzCaliforniazSanta Monica BayxPrevention. 0aPolitical activistszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aSewage disposal in the oceanxEnvironmental aspectszCaliforniazSanta Monica Bay. 70(DE-601)1042134930(DE-588)4006804-3aBiografie2gnd 70(DE-601)2225275360(DE-588)4434808-3aUmweltschützer2gnd 7aNATURE / Ecology.2bisacsh  a1985.  abays and oceans.  abeach.  abodies of water.  aclean water act.  aclean water.  addt.  adirty water.  adiscussion books.  aeasy to read.  aecology.  aengaging.  aenvironment.  aenvironmental impact.  aenvironmental movement.  aheal the bay.  ahuman impact.  ainsecticide pollution.  ainspirational.  alively.  alocal politics.  alos angeles.  amake a difference.  anonfiction account.  apolluted water.  araw sewage.  asanta monica b